WEBVTT

00:00:02.640 --> 00:00:04.643
It's Asguiaro Ebern.

00:00:05.018 --> 00:00:06.103
Getsuga...

00:00:06.978 --> 00:00:09.022
tensho!

00:00:10.481 --> 00:00:13.152
Why won't his Bankai disappear?!

00:00:13.609 --> 00:00:16.362
Help us... Ichigo...

00:00:16.821 --> 00:00:18.115
It's Hueco Mundo...

00:00:18.406 --> 00:00:19.783
Hueco Mundo is--!

00:00:20.366 --> 00:00:21.993
Quiet, please!

00:00:22.493 --> 00:00:24.287
Will you live or will you die?!

00:00:24.662 --> 00:00:27.499
We'll be having
a selection competition

00:00:27.499 --> 00:00:29.835
for the Hollows and Arrancar!

00:00:30.002 --> 00:00:32.003
You dare to speak poorly
of Master Halibel,

00:00:32.003 --> 00:00:34.715
and yet don't know who we are?!

00:00:44.348 --> 00:00:45.725
Are you guys really Qu--?

00:00:45.725 --> 00:00:48.561
Yes, we <i>are</i> who you think we are.

00:00:49.063 --> 00:00:50.522
We are <i>Quincies</i>.

00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:56.944
The Soul Society and Hueco Mundo
are being invaded by someone.

00:00:57.612 --> 00:01:00.698
And they are most likely... Quincies.

00:01:00.948 --> 00:01:03.534
Allow me to explain...

00:01:03.743 --> 00:01:05.995
The proper name for this form is...

00:01:06.746 --> 00:01:09.415
Quincy Voll Stern Dich.

00:01:09.875 --> 00:01:12.753
As Quincies extinguish more Hollows
in the World of the Living,

00:01:12.753 --> 00:01:16.215
the number of souls is diminished,
disrupting that natural balance...

00:01:16.924 --> 00:01:17.924
If we allow this to happen,

00:01:18.049 --> 00:01:20.677
the balance of souls
will eventually be ruined,

00:01:20.677 --> 00:01:23.180
causing the Soul Society to flow
into the World of the Living...

00:01:24.972 --> 00:01:27.558
ending in the simultaneous
destruction of both worlds.

00:01:27.893 --> 00:01:30.853
Everything that is happening now
stems from the fact that

00:01:31.355 --> 00:01:33.147
<i>you</i>, Head Captain,

00:01:33.147 --> 00:01:38.778
couldn't kill that man
1,000 years ago!

00:01:39.320 --> 00:01:40.989
Sklave Rai.

00:01:41.656 --> 00:01:44.534
If possible,
I didn't want to use this...

00:01:45.201 --> 00:01:50.581
because my holy wings would be
tarnished by such wicked beings.

00:02:00.133 --> 00:02:01.134
A Bankai...!

00:02:01.342 --> 00:02:02.969
If I destroy the disk on your head...

00:02:03.302 --> 00:02:05.430
you can't use that absolute
subordination of Reishi anymore,

00:02:05.430 --> 00:02:06.473
can you?!

00:02:06.764 --> 00:02:08.307
The Quincy Extermination Operation

00:02:08.432 --> 00:02:10.978
was finally carried out
200 years ago.

00:02:11.937 --> 00:02:15.649
The Soul Reapers and Quincies
have no other choice but to fight...

00:02:18.651 --> 00:02:22.781
Conflict is such
an unpleasant affair.

00:02:23.532 --> 00:02:24.741
What the hell...?

00:02:25.116 --> 00:02:27.995
Flaming pillars... of Reishi?

00:02:28.871 --> 00:02:29.955
Sorry...

00:02:30.872 --> 00:02:33.292
but our orders are to kill you all.

00:02:34.209 --> 00:02:35.836
Tremble in fear, Soul Reapers.

00:02:36.836 --> 00:02:39.840
The Stern Ritters are going to...

00:02:40.966 --> 00:02:42.884
purge all of you.

00:03:04.072 --> 00:03:08.784
{\an8}<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:03:08.993 --> 00:03:13.998
{\an8}<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:03:14.498 --> 00:03:18.878
{\an8}<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:03:19.170 --> 00:03:22.633
{\an8}<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:03:23.050 --> 00:03:29.014
{\an8}<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:03:29.348 --> 00:03:32.225
{\an8}<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:03:33.435 --> 00:03:38.481
{\an8}<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:03:38.731 --> 00:03:41.360
{\an8}<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:03:41.485 --> 00:03:45.989
{\an8}<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:03:46.114 --> 00:03:48.824
{\an8}<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:03:48.950 --> 00:03:53.788
{\an8}<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:03:53.913 --> 00:03:56.332
{\an8}<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:03:56.457 --> 00:03:58.377
{\an8}<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:03:58.377 --> 00:04:02.088
{\an8}<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:04:02.380 --> 00:04:06.050
{\an8}<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:04:06.175 --> 00:04:09.096
{\an8}<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:04:09.221 --> 00:04:13.809
{\an8}BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:04:26.321 --> 00:04:32.326
{\an8}THE SEIREITEI

00:04:32.326 --> 00:04:35.038
in 16 locations
within the Seireitei!

00:04:35.247 --> 00:04:36.915
They're already within
the Soul Shield Membrane!

00:04:36.915 --> 00:04:38.291
{\an8}FRONT OF SQUAD 9 BARRACKS –
PASSAGEWAY

00:04:38.291 --> 00:04:38.709
But how...?!

00:04:38.709 --> 00:04:40.209
Spiritual Pressures
belonging to Soul Reapers

00:04:40.209 --> 00:04:41.877
{\an8}SQUAD 6 BARRACKS – ALLEYWAY

00:04:41.877 --> 00:04:42.211
have disappeared
in several other locations!

00:04:42.211 --> 00:04:44.005
We believe they were
killed in combat!

00:04:44.298 --> 00:04:46.882
Squad 3's Lieutenant Kira's
Spiritual Pressure has vanished!

00:04:47.259 --> 00:04:49.218
Three seated officers of
the same squad have also vanished!

00:04:49.636 --> 00:04:52.930
25 squad members have perished
in West 601 District...!

00:04:52.930 --> 00:04:56.560
{\an8}KOKURYO GATE ENTRANCE

00:04:56.685 --> 00:04:57.810
{\an8}DEPARTMENT OF R&D – CONTROL ROOM

00:04:58.228 --> 00:04:59.646
<i>Over 1,000 dead
in just seven minutes</i>

00:04:59.646 --> 00:05:01.355
<i>since the start of the invasion...?!</i>

00:05:01.648 --> 00:05:02.524
<i>This is madness...</i>

00:05:03.190 --> 00:05:05.651
<i>There's no way
we can beat these guys!</i>

00:05:15.870 --> 00:05:17.788
Stop...!
We won't let you through!

00:05:18.915 --> 00:05:21.375
If you are scared,
feel free to run.

00:05:21.793 --> 00:05:24.379
I can't make a good example
out of any of you.

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:26.923
You dare mock
the 13 Court Guard Squads?!

00:05:27.423 --> 00:05:28.759
I told you to stop!

00:05:29.384 --> 00:05:30.552
Haven't you noticed?

00:05:30.968 --> 00:05:32.596
You're so overcome by fear that,

00:05:32.928 --> 00:05:34.514
since the beginning,
you've subconsciously been

00:05:34.514 --> 00:05:37.516
shifting the issue at hand from
life and death to dissuading me.

00:05:38.517 --> 00:05:41.646
But the war has already begun.

00:05:53.699 --> 00:05:59.663
{\an8}FRONT OF SQUAD 3 BARRACKS –
PASSAGEWAY

00:06:04.336 --> 00:06:06.213
I see... Understood.

00:06:08.548 --> 00:06:10.634
That didn't seem like good news.

00:06:11.468 --> 00:06:12.593
Did someone die?

00:06:13.845 --> 00:06:15.639
Is there a need to answer that?

00:06:17.807 --> 00:06:18.809
There is.

00:06:19.517 --> 00:06:20.685
The Spiritual Pressures
that disappeared just now

00:06:20.685 --> 00:06:22.144
came from Bazz-B's location.

00:06:22.853 --> 00:06:25.689
If there are survivors,
then it means that he messed up.

00:06:26.399 --> 00:06:27.817
{\an8}STERN RITTER "U"

00:06:28.276 --> 00:06:30.903
Finding faults between comrades?

00:06:31.362 --> 00:06:32.488
That's not art.

00:06:33.906 --> 00:06:38.536
I always get flashes of inspiration
whenever I look at Izuru.

00:06:39.329 --> 00:06:41.665
Just holding a guitar near him

00:06:41.790 --> 00:06:44.459
causes melodies
to flow out of me like tears.

00:06:45.127 --> 00:06:49.255
If Izuru is gone,
my guitar and I will be devastated.

00:06:49.755 --> 00:06:52.925
Sorry.
I know nothing about art.

00:06:53.427 --> 00:06:54.511
But don't worry...

00:06:54.970 --> 00:06:59.098
You and your guitar will never
get the chance to weep.

00:06:59.557 --> 00:07:01.976
Because you're going to die here
in five minutes.

00:07:02.644 --> 00:07:05.105
I guess you really don't know art.

00:07:05.689 --> 00:07:07.649
With the death of
so many of my men,

00:07:07.649 --> 00:07:09.985
no guitar wouldn't weep.

00:07:10.901 --> 00:07:13.487
My guitar and I
are already weeping.

00:07:14.656 --> 00:07:16.867
Don't assume you're
getting out of this alive...

00:07:17.617 --> 00:07:18.617
Quincy!

00:07:20.495 --> 00:07:21.495
{\an8}NEAR SQUAD 6 BARRACKS –
ROUND TOWER

00:07:23.581 --> 00:07:25.500
What kind of monster
is that thing?!

00:07:25.500 --> 00:07:27.334
What in the world is going on?!

00:07:27.586 --> 00:07:29.420
{\an8}STERN RITTER "F"

00:07:29.420 --> 00:07:31.548
None of our attacks are working...

00:07:32.673 --> 00:07:35.134
B-But that's not all...

00:07:38.430 --> 00:07:42.559
Why is everyone dying
screaming like that?!

00:07:46.687 --> 00:07:47.980
Don't retreat, you guys!

00:07:48.439 --> 00:07:50.483
The mission of
the 13 Court Guard Squads

00:07:50.483 --> 00:07:52.360
isn't to protect our own lives!

00:07:52.526 --> 00:07:55.613
It's to give our lives
to protect the Seireitei!

00:07:59.658 --> 00:08:01.702
We must not retreat!

00:08:05.122 --> 00:08:07.209
All right, well said!

00:08:07.584 --> 00:08:09.752
L-Lieutenant Abarai!

00:08:10.879 --> 00:08:12.880
Step aside and
leave the rest to me.

00:08:17.384 --> 00:08:18.010
{\an8}SQUAD 7'S GUARD AREA

00:08:19.678 --> 00:08:21.056
{\an8}STERN RITTER "E"

00:08:26.352 --> 00:08:29.523
Even a young girl like you
is fighting for the rebel army?

00:08:30.524 --> 00:08:32.775
They've made a doggy like you
a captain?

00:08:33.150 --> 00:08:35.403
You guys must be
seriously understaffed.

00:08:35.903 --> 00:08:37.572
The Soul Society, that is.

00:08:50.918 --> 00:08:52.169
<i>What's with this guy?!</i>

00:08:55.715 --> 00:08:59.260
<i>The moment he blocks,
some sort of marking appears...</i>

00:09:00.010 --> 00:09:01.554
<i>I'll try speeding up my attacks...</i>

00:09:10.522 --> 00:09:13.567
There's no need
to hold back, Renji.

00:09:14.525 --> 00:09:15.735
These people

00:09:15.860 --> 00:09:19.489
are trying to annihilate
the Soul Society without mercy.

00:09:19.655 --> 00:09:21.115
They are our enemies.

00:09:23.243 --> 00:09:24.952
Cut them down
with everything you've got.

00:09:25.287 --> 00:09:28.956
{\an8}DEPARTMENT OF R&D –
MAYURI KUROTSUCHI'S PRIVATE LAB

00:09:28.956 --> 00:09:30.457
{\an8}"TESTING"

00:09:30.457 --> 00:09:32.668
{\an8}"NEGATIVE"

00:09:33.003 --> 00:09:35.754
So they're <i>not</i> sealing away
one's Bankai?

00:09:37.423 --> 00:09:38.424
Captain...!

00:09:40.051 --> 00:09:41.052
Don't move.

00:09:42.553 --> 00:09:45.222
Captain!
Our swords won't penetrate them...!

00:09:45.724 --> 00:09:47.475
Our swords won't penetrate?

00:09:48.018 --> 00:09:49.394
That is not possible.

00:09:54.441 --> 00:09:56.025
What are you doing?!

00:09:56.359 --> 00:09:58.653
You shouldn't make
any careless movements either.

00:10:02.448 --> 00:10:05.118
W-What the hell?!

00:10:09.998 --> 00:10:11.707
Scatter, Senbonzakura.

00:10:39.068 --> 00:10:40.235
Are you serious?!

00:10:58.462 --> 00:10:59.464
Captain!

00:11:06.178 --> 00:11:10.140
{\an8}NEAR SQUAD 10 BARRACKS –
WAREHOUSE DISTRICT

00:11:16.563 --> 00:11:17.565
Captain!

00:11:17.565 --> 00:11:19.650
You can't use
that hand of yours anymore.

00:11:23.404 --> 00:11:25.948
Many of my comrades were killed...

00:11:26.533 --> 00:11:28.243
I have no intention
of holding back.

00:11:32.580 --> 00:11:34.666
<i>How is he... so tough?!</i>

00:11:40.504 --> 00:11:41.880
{\an8}SQUAD 2 BARRACKS –
CASTLE GATE CORRIDOR

00:11:43.006 --> 00:11:44.801
Suzumebachi can't pierce him?!

00:12:06.655 --> 00:12:07.990
Do you intend to use your Bankai?!

00:12:08.450 --> 00:12:11.452
Captain, according to
Lieutenant Sasakibe's report,

00:12:11.660 --> 00:12:14.456
they supposedly have a means
of sealing away Bankai!

00:12:14.788 --> 00:12:15.789
It's too dangerous!

00:12:15.956 --> 00:12:16.957
I'm aware of that.

00:12:17.500 --> 00:12:19.043
But these despicable people

00:12:19.168 --> 00:12:21.296
are responsible for
Lieutenant Sasakibe's death

00:12:21.671 --> 00:12:24.883
and caused bloodshed within
the Seireitei without warning.

00:12:26.259 --> 00:12:30.471
Moreover, they are foes we cannot
defeat without using Bankai...

00:12:31.514 --> 00:12:35.684
Which means that figuring out
a way to break that seal

00:12:35.684 --> 00:12:37.269
will be the key to this battle.

00:12:38.104 --> 00:12:39.272
Therefore, Renji...

00:12:41.399 --> 00:12:43.650
If my Bankai is sealed away,

00:12:44.277 --> 00:12:45.945
I want <i>you</i>
to finish them off with yours.

00:12:47.614 --> 00:12:48.655
Captain...!

00:12:54.453 --> 00:12:55.413
Bankai...

00:13:00.710 --> 00:13:02.669
Senbonzakura Kageyoshi...

00:13:13.972 --> 00:13:16.475
Kokujo Tengen Myo-oh!

00:13:16.975 --> 00:13:18.602
Jakuho Raikoben!

00:13:19.269 --> 00:13:21.022
Daiguren Hyorinmaru!

00:13:30.697 --> 00:13:31.615
We were wrong...

00:13:33.368 --> 00:13:34.660
This is <i>not</i> a seal!

00:13:45.587 --> 00:13:46.589
My Bankai...

00:13:48.549 --> 00:13:49.634
He stole it...!

00:14:09.445 --> 00:14:10.613
You've gotta be kidding me!

00:14:12.615 --> 00:14:14.366
She stole my Bankai?!

00:14:14.366 --> 00:14:17.327
Your Bankai is <i>mine</i> now, Doggy.

00:14:18.037 --> 00:14:19.496
I don't sense anything...

00:14:20.373 --> 00:14:21.456
Say something...

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:24.418
Say... anything!

00:14:25.336 --> 00:14:26.336
Hyorinmaru...!

00:14:27.964 --> 00:14:29.465
Hyorinmaru!

00:14:33.302 --> 00:14:34.303
Captain...

00:14:35.221 --> 00:14:36.471
What are you doing, Matsumoto...?

00:14:37.974 --> 00:14:39.225
Use Tenteikura!

00:14:39.350 --> 00:14:40.350
Hurry!

00:14:40.475 --> 00:14:42.477
Inform all the captains about this!

00:14:42.729 --> 00:14:44.605
Tell them <i>not</i> to use their Bankai!

00:14:45.148 --> 00:14:48.484
They don't seal Bankai...
they <i>steal</i> them!

00:14:48.985 --> 00:14:54.990
{\an8}"13 COURT GUARD SQUADS"

00:14:56.283 --> 00:14:57.409
Tenteikura!

00:15:03.666 --> 00:15:05.043
They can steal them...?!

00:15:07.754 --> 00:15:10.798
What are those fools doing?!

00:15:11.548 --> 00:15:14.552
It seems Squads 2, 6, and 7
have had theirs stolen as well...

00:15:15.345 --> 00:15:16.346
Those idiots!

00:15:16.511 --> 00:15:19.640
Why couldn't they wait until
my analysis was complete?!

00:15:19.932 --> 00:15:21.683
I can't believe their stupidity!

00:15:29.192 --> 00:15:31.527
I suppose... we should be grateful.

00:15:32.695 --> 00:15:36.032
With enough information,
Captain Kurotsuchi can usually

00:15:36.032 --> 00:15:39.369
come up with a solution
within a day.

00:15:39.952 --> 00:15:43.956
{\an8}SQUAD 8 BARRACKS – PERIPHERY

00:15:44.581 --> 00:15:48.586
We had no idea when we'd find out
what your abilities were.

00:15:50.087 --> 00:15:53.423
But you're not a foe
we can defeat without Bankai.

00:15:53.799 --> 00:15:59.304
Which means, sooner or later,
someone had to become a sacrifice.

00:16:04.268 --> 00:16:05.394
Grimmaniel...

00:16:12.567 --> 00:16:13.735
Well, what do you know...

00:16:14.111 --> 00:16:15.321
I tried putting on a brave face,

00:16:15.321 --> 00:16:17.490
but I guess I'm more disturbed
than I thought...

00:16:18.282 --> 00:16:19.826
This is a real problem, isn't it?

00:16:24.455 --> 00:16:25.999
D-Damn it...

00:16:26.499 --> 00:16:27.207
Bankai--

00:16:27.207 --> 00:16:28.292
Stop!

00:16:29.043 --> 00:16:32.046
We cannot afford to lose
your Bankai as well!

00:16:32.504 --> 00:16:34.090
B-But Captain...!

00:16:34.298 --> 00:16:39.595
Then how are we supposed to fight...

00:16:40.263 --> 00:16:42.557
against these guys?!

00:16:51.566 --> 00:16:53.651
Put me through to Ichigo Kurosaki!

00:16:53.942 --> 00:16:54.986
Huh?
Yes, sir...

00:16:55.278 --> 00:16:56.445
But we need
the Captain's permission--

00:16:56.445 --> 00:16:57.779
The Captain is on the front lines!

00:16:59.531 --> 00:17:01.200
I'll take full responsibility
for this.

00:17:03.869 --> 00:17:06.913
Yes?
Ah! Hello, Mr. Akon.

00:17:06.913 --> 00:17:08.458
It's been a while, hasn't it?

00:17:08.875 --> 00:17:10.585
How are things going over there?
I'm--

00:17:10.585 --> 00:17:12.836
<i>I told you it's an emergency!</i>

00:17:12.836 --> 00:17:15.298
<i>I need to talk to Ichigo Kurosaki!
Put me through to him!</i>

00:17:15.298 --> 00:17:17.008
Kurosaki?

00:17:17.008 --> 00:17:19.176
- That's not possible.
- <i>Why not?!</i>

00:17:19.176 --> 00:17:24.598
{\an8}"INCOMING CALL"

00:17:24.598 --> 00:17:25.682
<i>Hunt Army.</i>

00:17:29.644 --> 00:17:30.855
Damn it!

00:17:30.980 --> 00:17:32.440
It's still not working!

00:17:34.483 --> 00:17:37.653
<i>It seems the enemy
is trying to seal away</i>

00:17:37.653 --> 00:17:39.739
<i>Kurosaki's Bankai or something.</i>

00:17:40.073 --> 00:17:43.701
<i>But he's getting quite frustrated
because it's not working.</i>

00:17:43.701 --> 00:17:45.494
- What?!
- "It's not working"?!

00:17:47.913 --> 00:17:51.334
I know that the Soul Society
has been dealing with invaders.

00:17:51.959 --> 00:17:56.088
The fact that you contacted me
must mean things are quite serious.

00:17:56.713 --> 00:17:58.715
So let me go back
to my first question.

00:17:59.008 --> 00:18:02.553
{\an8}"INCOMING CALL"

00:18:03.512 --> 00:18:04.596
<i>Why?</i>

00:18:05.807 --> 00:18:10.310
<i>I'm using my Voll Stern Dich
and even absorbed that monster,</i>

00:18:10.310 --> 00:18:11.645
<i>so how is he able to...</i>

00:18:12.980 --> 00:18:15.316
<i>surpass me so easily?!</i>

00:18:28.412 --> 00:18:32.375
The guy I met the other day was
also trying to seal away my Bankai.

00:18:33.000 --> 00:18:36.253
Why do you want to seal away
my Bankai so badly?

00:18:36.503 --> 00:18:40.842
I'm not obligated
to give you an answer...

00:18:41.550 --> 00:18:45.471
Could it be that...
you guys are afraid of Bankai?

00:18:45.887 --> 00:18:47.597
Of course not!

00:18:47.848 --> 00:18:51.227
The Wandenreich fears nothing--!

00:18:55.940 --> 00:18:58.401
Thank you very much, Kurosaki.

00:18:58.401 --> 00:19:01.403
You were able to disrupt
the enemy's defensive Reishi,

00:19:01.403 --> 00:19:03.239
allowing me to deal a fatal blow.

00:19:03.364 --> 00:19:04.365
Mr. Urahara...!

00:19:05.157 --> 00:19:06.366
We have an emergency.

00:19:06.826 --> 00:19:09.162
Please head to
the Soul Society immediately.

00:19:09.452 --> 00:19:12.623
Ask Mr. Akon for the details
along the way.

00:19:13.958 --> 00:19:15.209
<i>Is this Ichigo Kurosaki?</i>

00:19:15.876 --> 00:19:17.461
<i>Listen carefully
without giving in to despair.</i>

00:19:18.461 --> 00:19:20.088
Pass this message
to the Secret Remote Unit!

00:19:20.213 --> 00:19:21.590
We have successfully
passed on the rescue request

00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:22.717
to Ichigo Kurosaki!

00:19:23.384 --> 00:19:26.220
Ichigo Kurosaki has already
escaped Hueco Mundo...

00:19:26.220 --> 00:19:27.555
<i>Everything's going to be okay now...</i>

00:19:27.846 --> 00:19:29.390
<i>He'll do something about this...</i>

00:19:29.557 --> 00:19:33.102
<i>I just know Mr. Ichigo
will save the Soul Society!</i>

00:19:37.440 --> 00:19:39.942
- Mr. Urahara!
- Ah, perfect timing!

00:19:40.151 --> 00:19:44.029
That corpse there should be
carrying a palm-sized metal plate.

00:19:44.321 --> 00:19:45.448
Please find it and bring it to me!

00:19:46.199 --> 00:19:48.326
Mr. Urahara...
Where's Kurosaki?

00:19:49.326 --> 00:19:52.371
I had Kurosaki
head to the Soul Society.

00:19:52.954 --> 00:19:54.624
I'll explain later!

00:19:54.874 --> 00:19:56.375
Right now,
I need to analyze the enemy!

00:19:58.752 --> 00:20:00.253
They can steal Bankai?!

00:20:00.630 --> 00:20:03.340
What are you talking about?
That's not possible--

00:20:03.340 --> 00:20:04.967
I don't want to believe it myself!

00:20:05.468 --> 00:20:08.136
But this is the information
we received

00:20:08.136 --> 00:20:09.763
<i>from the captains of
Squads 2, 6, 7, and 10,</i>

00:20:09.763 --> 00:20:11.307
<i>who have already had
their Bankai stolen.</i>

00:20:13.226 --> 00:20:14.727
<i>No way...</i>

00:20:19.315 --> 00:20:21.692
<i>Kurosaki,
I've analyzed the data I gathered</i>

00:20:21.817 --> 00:20:24.487
<i>from your earlier battle
with the enemy.</i>

00:20:25.153 --> 00:20:26.154
<i>Mr. Urahara?!</i>

00:20:26.614 --> 00:20:30.492
There are three major abilities
of note that the Quincies possess.

00:20:31.701 --> 00:20:35.248
The first is
the Quincy Voll Stern Dich.

00:20:35.873 --> 00:20:39.376
The second is the ability
he referred to as "Blut."

00:20:39.376 --> 00:20:43.047
By releasing Reishi
directly into their veins,

00:20:43.506 --> 00:20:47.134
they can drastically increase their
offensive and defensive abilities.

00:20:47.343 --> 00:20:50.096
It doesn't seem like they can use
both at the same time, though.

00:20:50.680 --> 00:20:53.182
And the third
and most important one is...

00:20:53.432 --> 00:20:55.183
<i>Bankai Plundering.</i>

00:20:55.768 --> 00:20:57.185
<i>The key thing here is that</i>

00:20:57.353 --> 00:21:01.356
your Bankai is the <i>only</i> one
they cannot steal.

00:21:02.107 --> 00:21:04.693
<i>At the moment,
the reason for that is--</i>

00:21:07.279 --> 00:21:08.280
What?!

00:21:10.825 --> 00:21:11.826
The exit!

00:21:12.451 --> 00:21:14.327
Mr. Urahara!
What's going on?!

00:21:15.121 --> 00:21:16.204
<i>Mr. Urahara!</i>

00:21:23.336 --> 00:21:26.673
<i>I let my guard down, thinking he'd
be dead from those injuries...</i>

00:21:27.215 --> 00:21:28.217
<i>But that's...</i>

00:21:28.342 --> 00:21:30.176
<i>Ransotengai!</i>

00:21:31.511 --> 00:21:33.513
I won't let him get there...

00:21:33.806 --> 00:21:36.392
The order given to me
by His Majesty was...

00:21:36.851 --> 00:21:38.602
to keep Ichigo Kurosaki at bay...

00:21:38.769 --> 00:21:41.564
even if it means my life!

00:21:46.818 --> 00:21:48.445
What the hell is this?!

00:21:51.574 --> 00:21:54.492
How unfortunate for you,
Ichigo Kurosaki!

00:21:55.076 --> 00:21:59.289
You were so close to reaching
the Soul Society to defend it.

00:21:59.999 --> 00:22:03.586
You no longer have the means
of escaping that prison.

00:22:04.627 --> 00:22:07.506
You lose, Ichigo Kurosaki.

00:22:07.631 --> 00:22:10.593
You will remain trapped
in that dark prison...

00:22:16.766 --> 00:22:22.104
where you must helplessly wait
until the Soul Society falls.

00:22:30.863 --> 00:22:33.865
{\an8}<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:34.032 --> 00:22:38.328
{\an8}<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:38.328 --> 00:22:42.750
{\an8}<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:42.875 --> 00:22:47.046
{\an8}<i>We lie buried as we glare
into the distance</i>

00:22:47.380 --> 00:22:50.007
{\an8}<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:50.132 --> 00:22:53.259
{\an8}<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:53.385 --> 00:22:55.721
{\an8}<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:55.887 --> 00:22:57.722
{\an8}<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:57.722 --> 00:22:58.807
{\an8}<i>Touching</i>

00:22:58.932 --> 00:23:02.353
{\an8}<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:23:02.353 --> 00:23:05.647
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:05.772 --> 00:23:11.945
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:23:12.320 --> 00:23:15.907
{\an8}<i>It cannot be undone
and cannot be stopped</i>

00:23:16.032 --> 00:23:19.494
{\an8}<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:23:19.494 --> 00:23:24.165
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:24.290 --> 00:23:26.335
{\an8}<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:26.544 --> 00:23:27.836
{\an8}<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:27.836 --> 00:23:32.590
{\an8}<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:32.715 --> 00:23:34.634
{\an8}<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:34.759 --> 00:23:36.511
{\an8}<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:37.680 --> 00:23:40.932
{\an8}<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:40.932 --> 00:23:47.355
{\an8}<i>The furthest reaches are now
visible to us</i>

00:23:47.355 --> 00:23:49.357
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:49.525 --> 00:23:51.317
{\an8}<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:51.317 --> 00:23:54.779
{\an8}<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:24:00.452 --> 00:24:03.998
<i>"The vow rests
in the shade of the willow."</i>

00:24:05.374 --> 00:24:08.501
<i>"Even as the lightning fades."</i>

